<p><b>Shillelagh</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Transmutation" title="Transmutation" class="mw-redirect">transmutation</a> <a href="/wiki/Cantrip" title="Cantrip" class="mw-redirect">cantrip</a> available to <a href="/wiki/Druid" title="Druid">druids</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-spellLists_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellLists-1">[2]</a></sup>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Description"> Description </span></h2>
<p>You use your bonus action to touch a club or quarterstaff. For the duration thereafter, you can use your spellcasting ability modifier instead of <a href="/wiki/Strength" title="Strength" class="mw-redirect">Strength</a> for the weapon, and its damage die becomes a d8. It also becomes a magical weapon if it isn't already. The spell ends if you cast it again or if you let go of the weapon.<sup id="cite_ref-spellDesc_0-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellDesc-0">[1]</a></sup>
</p>
